cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a hardware-software co-design architecture for binary code and runtime obfuscation to maintain application security and reduce an attacker's ability to exploit information. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the practicality of the system and its minimal overheads. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new architecture for secure execution. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses binary code diversification and self-reconfigurable processing elements. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the decoupling of program execution time, power, memory, and I/O activities from its functionality.
